    "title": "Sandbox Protocol: Constraint Verification and Containment in Autonomous Systems",
    "publication_date": "2026-04-24",
    "description": "The Sandbox Protocol formalizes constraint verification for autonomous intelligent systems operating in unbounded environments. We define sandboxing as a multi-layered enforcement mechanism operating across the Cognitive, Informational, and Physical layers, with real-time constraint monitoring, violation signaling, and mandatory rollback capabilities. This paper specifies the sandbox architecture, constraint definition languages, and enforcement semantics for deterministic autonomous operation.",
